ToC: spelling
Title: How do you spell <tt>mksh</tt>? How do you pronounce it?

<p>This <a href="@@RELPATH@@mksh.htm">shell</a> is spelt either
 ‚Äú<tt>mksh</tt>‚Äù (with, even at the beginning of a sentence, <a
 href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Capital_letters#Items_that_require_initial_lower_case">an
 initial lowercase letter</a>; this is important) or ‚ÄúMirBSD Korn Shell‚Äù,
 possibly with ‚Äúthe‚Äù.</p>
<p>I usually pronounce it as ‚Äú<span xml:lang="de-DE-1901">em-ka-es-ha</span>‚Äù,
 that is, the letters individually in my native German, emphasis on the
 first syllable, or say ‚ÄúMirBSD Korn Shell‚Äù, although it is manageable,
 mostly for Slavic speakers, to actually say ‚Äúmksh‚Äù as if it were a word ‚ò∫</p>
<p>Oh‚Ä¶ I‚Äôve run into this one, didn‚Äôt I? ‚ÄúMirBSD‚Äù is pronounced ‚Äú<span
 xml:lang="de-DE-1901">Mir-Be-Es-De</span>‚Äù germanically, for anglophones
 ‚ÄúMir-beas‚Äôtie‚Äù is fine.</p>
<p>This translates well into other languages, such as <span
 xml:lang="es">eme-ka-ese-ache</span> in Spanish, although English
 speakers may still find ‚ÄúMir-beastie korn shell‚Äù more palatable.</p>
